A search key allows for a fast method of finding a particular record. If you leave the search key empty, the system automatically creates a numeric number originating from a document sequence defined in the "Document Sequence" window. AD_FIELD.HELP:
This field allows the user to specify the interval of time between every incremental refresh of the master data (which includes business partners, products, tax information, ...). This time is specified in minutes.
The incremental refresh is much lighter, less expensive and therefore can be completed quicker than a total refresh, but will not detect deletions of master data records.

AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Time to fully refresh masterdata (in minutes)
AD_FIELD.HELP:
This field allows the user to specify the interval of time between every refresh of the master data (which includes business partners, products, tax information, ...). This time is specified in minutes.
The total refresh can be a very expensive operation, and if done too much frequently it can tax the server, and decrease the performance of all POS terminals, so it is strongly recommended to set it to a high value (60 minutes, or greater if possible).
So, if this field is set to 60, the master data will be refreshed every 60 minutes, if the user is logged in.
